 Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above.JOHANNESBURG - President Jacob Zuma is addressing the first Indigenous and Traditional Leaders Indaba.Zuma said South Africa has come a long way from colonial and apartheid rule.This was the president's first public appearance since this weekend's ANC NEC meeting at which he faced another challenge to his leadership.The objective of the indaba is to establish institutional mechanisms and create a platform for dialogue between the institution of traditional leadership, government and other stakeholders.Tweets about #TLIndaba FROM:@SikiGeyaMdingi since:2017-05-29 until:2017-05-30) eNCA